{"hits": {"hits": [{"created": "2026-04-20T19:35:02.313737+00:00", "modified": "2026-04-20T19:35:02.620991+00:00", "id": 19670309, "conceptrecid": "19670308", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19670309", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.19670308", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19670309", "metadata": {"title": "Bat-Plant Interaction and Their Impact in the Musal and Kurusadai Island Ecosystems of Gulf of Mannar, India", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19670309", "publication_date": "2011", "description": "(Uploaded by Plazi for the Bat Literature Project) The Gulf of Mannar is located in the southeastern tip of Tamilnadu extending from Rameswaram north to Kanyakumari south between 8\u00ba 48' N 78\u00ba 9 E and 9\u00ba 14' N 79'14 E South west coast comprises 21 islands. It is a priority area for conservation because of its richness of species and ecosystems, which support a large number of coastal marine life and public. Studies on the bat-plant interaction in Musal and Krusadai islands, which are the members of Mandapam group of islands were completed between the year 2010 and 2011. The observations so far, recorded a list of floral diversity depends on bats for propagation and pest management. The remarkable such and interactions are between Hipposideros, Megaderma, Cynopterus and Pteropus genus of bats and the floral diversity comprising mangrove tree spp., Thespesia populnea, Pandanus fascicularis, Tamarindus indica, Zizyphus nummularia, Borassus flabellifer, Syzygium cumnii, Ficus spp., Cordia spp. and Acacia spp. The bats depend on the plants for fruits, nectar and insect food. This interaction makes an important dependency for the survival of both the bat and plant diversity. The bat dispersed seeds effect recolonisation of the lost population of plant species diversity in the affected island parts. The observed bat visits with in the mangrove forest and the dry deciduous forest of the island shows the ecosystem services of bats. The studies on faecal pellet analysis has proved the insect bat's control over the Lepidopteran, Coleopteran, Dipteran, Hymnopteran and Chelicerata group of insect pests infects the flora of Musal and Krusadai islands. The evaluated importance of bat species interaction with the island ecosystem in turn needs special protection through conservation measures.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Vanitharani, Juliet", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jeyapraba, L", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bharathi, B Kavitha", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/3b032fc14c0851f0a320f249647abf85", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/1cff3e39ec7d4025c8fb142f9cc831d1129ab541cf9dd5fcfa06b5e408ed885b", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/4LQ7GSGU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/4LQ7GSGU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6c156db820931010e9844f919a808f0f!/b69175-71654", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/0157e8ec3f1f8eb877e7b6cd6fde26bc", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1 & 2", "pages": "35-44", "title": "Journal of Theoretical and Experimental Biology", "volume": "8"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/3b032fc14c0851f0a320f249647abf85"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:4LQ7GSGU"}], "communities": [{"i